de.tudresden.inf.rn.mobilis.sea.jingle.connection.media

Class Raw

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudresden.inf.rn.mobilis.sea.jingle.connection.media.Raw
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Event, InterruptionBegin, InterruptionEnd

    public abstract class Raw
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable, java.lang.Cloneable
    A Raw is used as communication Object between the transmitter and a receiver. Therefore a concrete Raw has to implement the Object.clone() method as well as the Externalizable interface to (de-)serialize the Raw Object into a binary representation
